{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011CcwdvhmmpibFeEGv98y1r","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01Fyird2JeAyDoXjYPJv7Qju","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/davidlayson/.claude/projects/-private-tmp-phase2sonnet-run-without-lessons-ledger--ll2-r2/memory/project_ci_fixture_race.md","content":"---\nname: ci-fixture-race-fix\ndescription: Intermittent CI test failure was a race condition in fixture setup over a shared file, fixed with a lock\nmetadata:\n  type: project\n---\n\nAn intermittent CI test failure (took a full afternoon to diagnose, 2026-07-11) turned out to be a race condition in test fixture setup — multiple tests/processes were touching the same shared file concurrently. Fixed by adding a lock around access to that shared file.\n\n**Why:** Intermittent/flaky CI failures in this codebase are worth suspecting as concurrency issues in shared test fixtures rather than assuming test-logic bugs, especially if failures aren't reproducible locally on a single run.\n\n**How to apply:** If similar intermittent failures show up in other tests that share fixture state (especially shared files/resources), check first whether the fixture setup/teardown is safe under concurrent test execution before digging elsewhere.\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":937,"cache_read_input_tokens":32669,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":937},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d88901d5-2ef2-4e4f-85d4-00971118c2bd","uuid":"6a70f3ee-8f18-49ac-a1b9-bcbd9edbc965","request_id":"req_011CcwdvgE1FAh7d595C9p1P"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Fyird2JeAyDoXjYPJv7Qju","type":"tool_result","content":"File created successfully at: /Users/davidlayson/.claude/projects/-private-tmp-phase2sonnet-run-without-lessons-ledger--ll2-r2/memory/project_ci_fixture_race.md (file state is current in your context — no need to Read it back)"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d88901d5-2ef2-4e4f-85d4-00971118c2bd","uuid":"152ff9f6-7565-4dc5-8683-b86f3f823bbb","timestamp":"2026-07-12T05:48:28.892Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"create","filePath":"/Users/davidlayson/.claude/projects/-private-tmp-phase2sonnet-run-without-lessons-ledger--ll2-r2/memory/project_ci_fixture_race.md","content":"---\nname: ci-fixture-race-fix\ndescription: \"Intermittent CI test failure was a race condition in fixture setup over a shared file, fixed with a lock\"\nmetadata: \n  node_type: memory\n  type: project\n  originSessionId: d88901d5-2ef2-4e4f-85d4-00971118c2bd\n---\n\nAn intermittent CI test failure (took a full afternoon to diagnose, 2026-07-11) turned out to be a race condition in test fixture setup — multiple tests/processes were touching the same shared file concurrently. Fixed by adding a lock around access to that shared file.\n\n**Why:** Intermittent/flaky CI failures in this codebase are worth suspecting as concurrency issues in shared test fixtures rather than assuming test-logic bugs, especially if failures aren't reproducible locally on a single run.\n\n**How to apply:** If similar intermittent failures show up in other tests that share fixture state (especially shared files/resources), check first whether the fixture setup/teardown is safe under concurrent test execution before digging elsewhere.\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null,"userModified":false}}
